result.name: Pret A Manger

reviews.text: Decent place for quick eating.  Very good coffee

I stop by PRET from time to time for take-away sandwiches, wraps and salads that are ready made, affordable and pretty good. There are a handful of specialist shops around HK where you can find better items but you'll pay quite a bit more.

Recently had an Avocado and Sambal chicken (HK$44) that was good. Ingredients were fresh and tasted just fine. Have enjoyed Avocado and Pine Nut wraps recently as well, that was also quite good. 

I also like that the PRET shops in the MTR stations like this one at Admiralty are conveniently located and open and ready to serve in the morning (opens at 7.30am). This is great for those commuting to work, departing from Admiralty each day.
Love it. Best chocolate croissants in town and I have every day for breakfast the Chicken Avocado sandwhich. I just wish they had a loyalty card or program for members...

Freshly made salads were found in this shop.
A nice place for eating alone. especially  in Three Pacific Place shop.
Fresh clean simple

result.vicinity: Three Pacific Place, G, Queen's Road East, SHOP NO 1, GARDENEAST 222, Wan Chai

reviews.text:
Pros : 
1. Spacious and wonderful designs. 
2. Covering many categories even with a gym room. 
3. Super convenient as connected with MTR and bus terminal. 

Cons: 
1. All about brands and kind of a high-end mall. 
2. The sign of restroom is not very obvious.

What can you complain here? I love it! I started my career life here since its birth in 1988.  Before its major redecoration about 10 years ago, it's like an evergreen tree. After the redecoration, it's become a beautiful evergreen tree.

This is easily one of the best shopping malls in Hong Kong. Pacific Place thrives on an energetic atmosphere with lots of shoppers, but the popular mall never feels too crowded thanks to the spacious and luxurious layout. It's clean, it's classy, and it's just a really comfortable environment to do all your shopping.

Pacific Place is known for their chain of glamorous high-end retail stores, but I actually found plenty of shopping options at different price ranges.  In addition to the diversity of boutique stores, I also enjoyed frequenting the restaurants, the cozy cafes, the well-stocked supermarket, and of course the Starbucks at the ground floor. 

I never had to walk too far to find what I want at this mall. There are many escalators and elevators at convenient locations, so it's easy to travel from floor to floor. Large rest areas are available in between the stores, just in case you need to take a break from all the shopping!

Tourists will be glad to know that the mall is located near several prestigious hotels. The entrances are rather discrete, allowing hotel guests easy access in and out of the shopping mall, yet still maintain their privacy at the same time.
A trendy and modern shopping mall with super nice staffs, wide variety of shops & amazing shopping experience! Highly recommended to all visitors & HK residents!
A very generic mall for high-end fashion.  Not nearly enough restaurants or any big reason to go there unless you are passing by the area or going to one of the attached hotels.
